1 SECTION 29. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
2 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
3 SHARED SERVICES. (a)(1) The Chief Fiscal Officer of the State may create a
4 Shared Services paying accounts on his or her books and on the books of the
5 Treasurer of State and the Auditor of State for the payment of personal
6 services and operating expenses in the Shared Services Paying Account
7 Appropriation by the Department of Parks, Heritage, and Tourism.
8 (2) The Chief Fiscal Officer of the State shall direct the transfer
9 of funds and appropriations to the Shared Services Paying Account
10 appropriation section of this act on the books of the Treasurer of State, the
11 Auditor of State, and the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State.
12 (3) The transfer authority provided to the department in
13 subdivision (a)(2) of this section may be used to make transfers only within
14 the department's appropriation act or between other appropriation acts
15 authorized for the department.
16 (4) The provisions of this section shall be in effect from the date
17 of passage through June 30, 2025 2026.
